Description:
Propak Systems Ltd.
is an established leader in engineering, fabrication, and construction of gas compression, gas processing, and heavy oil facilities, and is actively advancing the development of products related to the decarbonization of energy production. By integrating comprehensive engineering services and first-in-class modular fabrication capacity with complete construction services, Propak designs and builds industry-leading hydrocarbon processing facilities for installation around the world.
Project Engineers
lead the coordination of project execution in accordance with client requirements and objectives, within cost and schedule constraints, and in adherence to quality procedures and practices.
Key Responsibilities:
Work independently and with teams to manage small and intermediate-size projects in the design of oil and gas processing equipment, heavy oil plant facilities, carbon capture facilities, waste heat recovery units, and hydrogen generation facilities;
Provide technical direction and coordination of multi-discipline functions or areas within the project scope encompassing engineering, drafting, procurement, fabrication, construction, and commissioning (as applicable);
Serve as a technical management team member on large EPFC projects;
Project management;
Supervise, train, coach, and mentor project engineers-in-training, engineering technologists, and co-op students on a temporary, task level basis;
Participate in Bid / Evaluate / Award process including development of Request for Quotation (RFQ) packages, bid evaluations, and Bill of Material (BOM) entry into Enterprise Resource Planning software;
Collaborate with various engineering and drafting disciplines to achieve project objectives;
Manage interfaces with key project stakeholders;
Ensure that the level of performance is in accordance with contract specifications, within budget limits, and that the execution of the project progresses as set down in the contract and the project schedules;
Manage project scope and coordinate change management submissions and processes;
Facilitate 3D model reviews and construction planning meetings;
Participate in Piping and Instrumentation Drawing (P&ID) reviews and Hazard and Operability Studies (HAZOPs);
Prepare and maintain line, equipment, instrumentation, P&ID, and specialty items lists;
Coordinate and assist with the sizing and selection of project instrumentation and process equipment;
Maintain project schedule;
Liaise with Project Planners-Schedulers and Project Cost Controls personnel to prepare reports on project status and progress on a regular basis;
Check vessel, structural steel, piping spooling, assembly, and civil drawings against project requirements;
Interact with purchasing and expediting to follow up on buyouts;
Review and approve vendor drawings and documents for accuracy in accordance with design requirements and specifications;
Assist with resolutions of shop and field Requests for Information (RFIs);
Conduct shop inspections and resolve Nonconformance Reports (NCRs);
Respond to queries and issues pertaining to project;
Coordinate and review the compilation of Project Data and Operating Manuals for distribution to the project team and client;
Qualifications:
Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical or Chemical Engineering from an accredited university
Registered, or eligible for registration, with the Association of Professional Engineers and Geoscientists of Alberta (APEGA)
5+ years of directly-related experience in design of oil and gas processing equipment or heavy oil plant facilities in the Canadian context
Familiarity with conducting Piping and Instrumentation Drawing (P&ID) reviews
Experience with design, installation, and operation of refineries or oil and gas processing equipment including refrigeration, turbo-expander, or amine treating plants is an asset
Experience in a fabrication environment is an asset
Experience within an EPC and EPCM work environment is an asset
Experience in instrumentation, oil and gas equipment sizing, and the packaging of compressor equipment is an asset
Experience with carbon capture, hydrogen production, or waste heat recovery is an asset
Propak offers competitive compensation and a comprehensive benefits package including 3 weeks of vacation and 8 float days per year.
